   "body" : "Moving the kernel sanity check code to kernel context instantiation time ensures that it is impossible to create an invalid kernel context. This is based on a suggestion made in a [comment](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/25065#discussion_r882182549) by @theuni in the [original pull request](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/25065) first introducing the `kernel::Context`.\r\n\r\nSince this touches the daemon initialization logic, also fix a bug where it would be possible for a termination signal to he handled by an uninstantiated interrupt object and thus causing a segfault. The kernel context initialization is moved to a point as early as possible in the code. The possible segfault can be reproduced by manually inserting a `raise(SIGTERM);`between the call to `AppInitBasicSetup` and `kernel::Context` construction in `bitcoind.cpp`.",
